# Website Mini Project Assignment

## Objective
Create a simple website using HTML and CSS, following a modular structure. You will separate the code for the header, dashboard, footer, and main body into different files and link them together in `index.html`.

---

## Folder Structure

```
website_mini_project/
│
├── public/
│   ├── logo/
│   │   ├── logo.png
│   │   └── favicon.ico
│   └── images/
│       └── products/
│           └── apple.png
│
├── index.html
│
├── styles/
│   └── style.css
│
├── header/
│   ├── header.html
│   └── styles/
│       └── header.css
│
├── footer/
│   ├── footer.html
│   └── styles/
│       └── footer.css
│
└── dashboard.html
```

---

## Assignment Tasks

### 1. **Create the Folder Structure**
- Replicate the above folder structure in your project directory.

### 2. **Header Component**
- In `header/header.html`, write the HTML code for your website's header (e.g., logo, navigation links).
- Style the header in `header/styles/header.css`.

### 3. **Footer Component**
- In `footer/footer.html`, write the HTML code for your website's footer (e.g., copyright).
- Style the footer in `footer/styles/footer.css`.

### 4. **Dashboard Component**
- Create `dashboard.html` for the dashboard section (e.g., product listings, user info).
- You may add a separate CSS file for dashboard styles if needed.

### 5. **Main Body**
- The main content (body) should be written in `index.html`.

### 6. **Global Styles**
- Use `styles/style.css` for global styles (e.g., fonts, colors).

### 7. **Assets**
- Place images and logos in the appropriate folders under `public/`.

---

## How to Link Components in `index.html`

To include header, dashboard, and footer in `index.html`, use the HTML `<iframe>` or [HTML5 `<object>`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/object) tag, or use JavaScript to load components dynamically.

**Example using `<iframe>`:**
```html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Website Mini Project</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="header/styles/header.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="footer/styles/footer.css">
    <link rel="icon" href="public/logo/favicon.ico">
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Header -->
    <iframe src="header/header.html" style="width:100%; border:none; height:100px;"></iframe>

    <!-- Dashboard -->
    <iframe src="dashboard.html" style="width:100%; border:none; height:400px;"></iframe>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <iframe src="footer/footer.html" style="width:100%; border:none; height:80px;"></iframe>
</body>
</html>
```

**Or, using JavaScript (advanced):**
```html
<!-- index.html -->
<body>
    <div id="header"></div>
    <div id="dashboard"></div>
    <div id="footer"></div>

    <script>
        fetch('header/header.html')
            .then(res => res.text())
            .then(data => document.getElementById('header').innerHTML = data);

        fetch('dashboard.html')
            .then(res => res.text())
            .then(data => document.getElementById('dashboard').innerHTML = data);

        fetch('footer/footer.html')
            .then(res => res.text())
            .then(data => document.getElementById('footer').innerHTML = data);
    </script>
</body>
```

---

## Submission

- Submit your entire `website_mini_project` folder.
- Ensure all components are properly linked and styled.
- Your website should display the header, dashboard, and footer as separate components.

---

## Tips

- Keep your code organized and modular.
- Use comments in your HTML and CSS files.
- Test your website in a browser to ensure all links and styles work.

---

**Good luck!**